# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Revolution Trading Pros — root .env example (workspace-wide overview)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# This file is informational. Real secrets live in:
#   - api/.env             (Rust API; read by std::env::var at boot)
#   - frontend/.env.local  (frontend dev overrides; gitignored)
#   - frontend/.env.production (committed; safe public values only)
#
# For local development against the Docker stack, copy this template:
#   cp .env.example .env
# …or skip it entirely — docker-compose.yml ships sane defaults.
#
# Production secrets are managed via:
#   - Fly.io secrets:  `fly secrets set -a revolution-trading-pros-api KEY=value`
#   - Cloudflare Pages: dashboard → Settings → Environment variables
#
# Each variable is documented in the per-service example file. The root file
# only lists the ones that affect the local stack via docker-compose.yml.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── docker-compose overrides (optional; defaults are fine for first boot) ──

# JWT signing secret used by the local API container.
# docker-compose.yml falls back to a long dev placeholder; override here for
# a stable local secret across container rebuilds.
JWT_SECRET=

# Stripe test keys. Without these, payment endpoints return errors but the
# rest of the stack works.
STRIPE_SECRET=
STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
